            There are two steps involved in the basic workflow for accepting a deal proposal as-is:

                - List available deals, 
                - Purchase a selected deal.


            #### 2.1.1 List available deals

            To list all available deals, Send a GET request to the /deals/proposals endpoint:

            ```
            $ curl -X GET \
                -H 'IXM-UserID: 1234' \
                -H 'IXM-AccessToken: oFimaL5gCz9yJq2IKenrev2pclk5ul7P' \
                https://market.indexexchange.com/api/v1/deals/proposals
            ```

            In response, a list of available deal proposals is returned. Responses may differ based on:

                - Filters. A response may optionally be filtered by any of the available filters described in the deal proposals route.
                - Pagination maximums. The pagination object specifies the requested maximum objects and the current page offset. The number of available deals returned is limited to the pagination maximum.

