            #### 2.1.2 Accept the deal

            Our simplified example illustrates two proposals available for purchase: 1“Great deal”1 and 1“Superfab Ultradeal”1. Let’s assume 1“Superfab Ultradeal”1 is perfect and we agree with all terms in the proposal. 
            We can accept this deal as-is by sending a PUT request to /deals/active. The body of the request is a JSON object containing the proposal ID:

            ```
            $ curl -X PUT \
                -H 'IXM-UserID: 1234' \
                -H 'IXM-AccessToken: oFimaL5gCz9yJq2IKenrev2pclk5ul7P' \
                -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
                -d '{ "proposalID": 888 }' \
                https://market.indexexchange.com/api/v1/deals/active
            ```

            We now have an active deal named “Superfab Ultradeal” which is available for bidding starting on September 9th, 2017. 

